<div id="review_2026424247" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2026424247" />
    <a title="Emily" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49847688-emily"><img alt="Emily" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1502386968p2/49847688.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2026424247?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emily" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emily" href="/user/show/49847688-emily">Emily</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2026424247" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11764449055152106533">I&apos;m leaving this unrated because while it was in many ways a beautiful book, it&apos;s also the most upsetting book I&apos;ve ever read.<br/><br/>Obviously, content warnings abound. This book contains child molestation, sexual assault, murder, abuse, among other things.<br/><br/>Because Marzano-Lesnevich contrasts the child molester and murderer with events in her own life, there is an intimacy throughout the story. I&apos;ve read true crime before, I&apos;ve seen true crime documentaries, but because this book&apos;s structure it felt so </span>
  <span id="freeText11764449055152106533" style="display:none">I'm leaving this unrated because while it was in many ways a beautiful book, it's also the most upsetting book I've ever read.<br /><br />Obviously, content warnings abound. This book contains child molestation, sexual assault, murder, abuse, among other things.<br /><br />Because Marzano-Lesnevich contrasts the child molester and murderer with events in her own life, there is an intimacy throughout the story. I've read true crime before, I've seen true crime documentaries, but because this book's structure it felt so much more personal, and therefor so much more horrifying. <br /><br />Marzano-Lesnevich writing feels quiet. It's this quiet that left me feeling so devastated. <br /><br />I'm not sure if I would recommend this. It's beautiful, but it has left me unsettled in a way that no other book has. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11764449055152106533" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


