<div id="review_2592602822" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2592602822" />
    <a title="Kimberly Dawn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35812962-kimberly-dawn"><img alt="Kimberly Dawn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1563040664p2/35812962.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2592602822?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kimberly Dawn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kimberly Dawn" href="/user/show/35812962-kimberly-dawn">Kimberly Dawn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2592602822" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3982012135027237627">I felt this book was well balanced in covering both the author’s childhood sexual abuse as well as the story of the murder of a child by a pedophile, Ricky Langley, who was the victim of his own traumatic childhood. She covers the family lives of all involved, including her own. <br/><br/>Learning of the pedophile Ricky Langley and the 1992 murder of six-year-old Jeremy Guillory triggered Alexandria’s own unresolved issues. <br/>Writing this book enabled her to come to terms somewhat with her childhood trauma.</span>
  <span id="freeText3982012135027237627" style="display:none">I felt this book was well balanced in covering both the author’s childhood sexual abuse as well as the story of the murder of a child by a pedophile, Ricky Langley, who was the victim of his own traumatic childhood. She covers the family lives of all involved, including her own. <br /><br />Learning of the pedophile Ricky Langley and the 1992 murder of six-year-old Jeremy Guillory triggered Alexandria’s own unresolved issues. <br />Writing this book enabled her to come to terms somewhat with her childhood trauma.<br /><br />The author still struggled with the silence and the overall lack of compassion demonstrated by her parents for the long lasting effects of sexual abuse which was inflicted by her maternal grandfather. Although her parents were educated lawyers, it was as if they didn’t want to dwell on the past, and they chose not to confront her grandfather. They did make efforts and arrangements so the grandfather would no longer be left alone with or in a position to continue the abuse. <br /><br />Learning about the complicated and deeply flawed family dynamics of these various families held my interest. These tragic stories deserve to be told. <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3982012135027237627" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


